                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Cleveland</placeName>\n                <date>May 6<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1857. 5617</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>Rev &amp; Dear Friend</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">I am duly in receipt of<lb/> your esteemed favor bearing date of the\n                    <date>3d</date><lb/> inst this morning and regret that I am<lb/> in possession\n                of the desired information<lb/> that might otherwise delay an immediate<lb/> answer.\n                Our mutually valued friend <persName>Alfred<lb/> T. Jones Esq.</persName> wrote us a\n                very eloquent letter some<lb/> time since in reference to the subject you have<lb/>\n                ably advocated and the trial we then made<lb/> to obtain loans from our\n                co-religionist re-<lb/>-sulted only in upraidings and derision.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Not I assure you without just cause. The<lb/> congregation to which\n                we belong is in debt<lb/> to the amount of $2000. for building &amp; balance<lb/> of\n                money due on lot It consists of only 20<lb/> members upon whom from the\n                beginning<lb/> all the responsibility and liability has<lb/> devolved. We have been\n                but recently threat<lb/>-ened with a suit of ejectment which<lb/> caused us all to\n                bleed to our uttermost pe<lb/>-cuniarily the poorest among us advancing<lb/> a $100.\n                but we still have the heavy<lb/> burden of $2000 hanging o'er our necks<lb/> and\n                weighing us down with more</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3dv1d78p/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
