                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>-fying<lb/> it must be to you after so many long years to<lb/> once more and that to\n                in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> assume<lb/> the exalted office it has been\n                your destiny to<lb/> so ably fill, permit me to congratulate you.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I cannot express to you the real plea-<lb/>sure—the very <hi\n                    rend=\"underline\">thought</hi> of your return affords<lb/> to my heart, believe\n                me I hail it with no<lb/> ordinary emotions of pride and gratification<lb/> of\n                course at present perhaps forever the “Advo-<lb/>-cate” will be abandoned—your\n                ministerial<lb/> duties and your editorial not permitting ad<lb/>-ditional—at least\n                at present, perhaps it is<lb/> as well, the generation to come will be a more<lb/>\n                intelligent one. I mean of our people in this<lb/> country, and they will require a\n                literature<lb/> of their own. I shall forthwith consti-<lb/>tute myself your active\n                agent here for your<lb/> admirable journal the occident and as<lb/> meet “our\n                people” weekly now at the lodge,<lb/> being a member of the I.O.BB. I shall\n                have<lb/> opportunities which shall not be lost. I<lb/> begin by sending you the\n                name of<lb/>\n                <persName>D. Cauffman</persName> to whom from <date>1<hi rend=\"sup\">st</hi> of\n                    May</date><lb/> you may send the Occident <del>for one year</del><lb/> I shall\n                exert myself in your further<lb/> behalf in this respect on every occasion<lb/> and\n                the pleasure of this aiding to</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3dv1d78p/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
