                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3dv1d78p/manifest/annotation/p4",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>disseminate the doctrines promulgated <del>in you</del><lb/> through your journal,\n                will be “sweet recompense<lb/> for all my labors.” It may be that I may<lb/> in some\n                of my “inspired moments” send<lb/> you a fledgling for the grave columns of<lb/> the\n                Occident but it will much depend<lb/> upon “time” and the “will” to do anything<lb/>\n                that smacks of literary recreation or labor.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Your friends here who esteem you so warm<lb/>-ly beg me to assure\n                you of the gratification<lb/> your return to the pulpit will afford<lb/> them. Both\n                    <persName>Mr &amp; Mrs Davis</persName> desire (with<lb/> my Brother &amp;\n                    <add>?</add>) to be kindly<lb/> remembered. Thank God our little ones<lb/> have\n                come through the “fire &amp; water” of their<lb/> recent long &amp; painful not to\n                say serious<lb/> sickness in safety the gloom that has<lb/> so long hung over our\n                household is fast<lb/> disappearing under the blessed and<lb/> benigrant<add>?</add>\n                rays of returning Health &amp; Sunshine<lb/> With renewed assurances of esteem\n                and<lb/> regard believe me</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(8)\">Very truly &amp; warmly</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(9)\">your friend</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(9)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">B F. Peixotto</persName>\n            </p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
